    {
      "title": "Precinct Fog",
      "lines": [
        "The old precinct went quiet the night the lamps drowned. Now the fog owns it.",
        "Back into the corner — south wall and east wall are stone. Watch the north and the west.",
        "Five nights. You won't see them until they're on you. Some don't bother with the walls at all."
      ],
